Since TiddlyWiki Version 5.1.4, it's possible to apply customs styles with `data-` attributes. see: [[How to apply custom styles]]

The [[Custom data-styles]] stylesheet tiddler contains the following definition:

```
[data-tags*="data-tags-hardlinebreaks"] .tc-tiddler-body {
  word-break: normal; 
  word-wrap: break-word;
  white-space: pre-wrap;
}
```

